pageContext.claim: “They just happened to find 50,000 ballots late last night. The USA is embarrassed by fools. Our Election Process is worse than that of third world countries!”
pageContext.analysis: Gabriel Sterling, a top Georgia elections official, quickly tweeted back to Trump that he is wrong: "No Mr. President, there weren't “found” ballots. We have known the number of advanced votes since this weekend. We saw record Election Day turnout. As of Monday 970,000 absentees had been accepted. 31k more were added in yesterday’s totals. That leaves 60k that came in yesterday."
